<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-798-526  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 798 526.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Oct 10 1989 v3 n36 p26(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Smalltalk-80 2.5 gets runtime kit. (Smalltalk-80 object orientedprogramming language)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Said, Carolyn.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   ParcPlace Systems Inc. (product development).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)Objectworks for Smalltalk-80 (Program development software)(product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Object-Oriented LanguagesProgram Development ToolsUpgradingApplications Programming.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Carolyn SaidandM;Mountain View, Calif.andP;  -- ParcPlace Systems recently upgraded its version ofSmalltalk-80, making the object-oriented programming language viable fordeveloping commercial software, according to the company.andM;Version 2.5, which is being marketed under the new name Objectworks forSmalltalk-80, adds a runtime tool kit &quot;so people can actually deliverapplications as opposed to using the system as an exploratory tool,&quot; saidDoug Pollack, ParcPlace vice president of marketing and sales.andM;Other new features include an on-line tutorial and the ability to portgraphical applications across Mac, MS-DOS and Unix operating systems withoutrecompilation.andM;Jim Heddens, manager of Anderson Consulting of New York, uses Smalltalk-80 tobuild demonstrations of graphical user interface concepts for his clients.andO;&quot;The runtime tool kit will be a big help,&quot; he said.andP;  &quot;We have a hard timeporting demos around.andP;  Clients don't usually have a Mac with 8 Mbytesavailable to run them.&quot;andM;Objectworks for Smalltalk-80, available now, sells for $595, down from $995for the previous release.andP;  Upgrades are $149.andM;ParcPlace Systems is located at 1550 Plymouth St., Mountain View, Calif.andO;94043; (415) 691-6700; (800) 882-7880.andO;</TEXT></DOC>